[{"id":"6f5862419ae0283c7c45aa66a05bcd71","from":"Lookout Mobile Security","from_email":"feedback@email.lookout.com","to":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","to_list":[{"name":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"Security Alert: Researchers find critical iOS vulnerabilities","date":"2016-08-25T17:15:22.000Z","formatted_date":"Aug 25, 2016","formatted_time":"5:15 PM","body":" \n\n\nLookout and our research partner Citizen Lab have discovered a critical threat known as Pegasus that affects mobile devices, including iOS. We take our promise of securing your device seriously, so we\u2019re reaching out to all Lookout iOS users to explain the risk and inform you of the steps you should take to protect your device.\n\nWhat is Pegasus?\n\nPegasus is a sophisticated attack that uses three vulnerabilities in the iOS software, collectively known as Trident, that, when exploited, enables attackers to install spyware on your device. Once installed, this spyware can access your personal messages, camera, phone calls, emails as well as various apps that may also be on your device, including Gmail, Facebook, Skype, WhatsApp, Viber, FaceTime, Calendar, Line, Mail.Ru, WeChat, SS, Tango, and others.\n\nHow do I protect myself?\n\nTo make sure you're protected against Pegasus, we recommend following these steps:\n\n\n\n1.\n\n Update your iOS operating system immediately to 9.3.5, which includes a recently released fix from Apple. To do so, go to Settings, tap \u2018General\u2019, then \u2018Software Update\u2019, and then \u2018Install Now\u2019.\n\n\n2.\n\nYou should also update your Lookout app to the latest version and then open the app and check the System Advisor in the Security module to determine if your device is secure.\n\n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=66467b9e77c70700265559910c9b7dc4f5157af4b866607c3e58e4e876214b5e450274c74a6de6fc \nUpdate Lookout Now \n\n\nIf you are impacted, you should contact Lookout directly for assistance with remediation. You can check out our \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=66467b9e77c70700e6e7157a46e461b731c0c61bc2bdee9ff36a6b87bb6ae2d17975d4241b26ecf8 \nblog  for additional details about this threat or contact our support team at \nmailto:support@lookout.com \nsupport@lookout.com .\n\n\n\nTo learn more about how Lookout can protect your enterprise against threats such as Pegasus, visit \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=66467b9e77c707006d13de309dbd26679dc68227d8e9db4950144d8dcd3481c2ba8c6ebc943464d2 \nour enterprise blog post .\n\nYour Account Information:\n\nEmail address: jeeproject@yahoo.com\n\nDevice type: iPhone41\n\nPhone number ending in: no phone number on record\n\n\n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=66467b9e77c70700e80b06182ab89f92f57aed6be102aa29dfd73a971edda10a93db5533172d88db \nLearn more about Lookout \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=66467b9e77c7070010c9c36bf95300e2deef0f5671d681c0421ff8d334fe3f50c75faceed8a52903 \n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=66467b9e77c707007893a4268f1a909ad38a759b1a279eb9ca1148eaab8b06c06934a56d55e68040 \n\n\u00a9 2016 Lookout, Inc. \u2219 One Front St. Suite 2700 \u2219 San Francisco, CA 94111\n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=66467b9e77c7070085d4f69cf0f6609da1045f3260dac3fed29b8f4f31b0f8f0579fa1f5306595e6 \nManage Profile  \u00b7 \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=66467b9e77c707004646a8b64aba5067370ab01916644eb0cfbf695c8505abc5b31e68ac33f4a3d7 \nPrivacy  \u00b7 \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=66467b9e77c7070082b21e5be369e2e59149fa8de642a0e07277342dcd8837e4fa0a9985f0e2a74d \nTerms and Conditions  \u00b7 \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/unsub_center.aspx?qs=3cb13e60d698b9d48aff2a2d76447cb7af61f9ed936c040dab70e612670abadf6f60638558b5850910a7c0f4242cd957b6937b5d2fbd057390269fceca65789e \nUnsubscribe \n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/profile_center.aspx?qs=3cb13e60d698b9d489d19bac7c23c2d83427f873ef28b23675575e47b00b5eea354876cce2d99ba4492742ec1c10c18b0d724c529bb5e1ee5fc7e3f8fd9d87a3 \n\n\n \n","bo